New York City to Finally Lift COVID-19 Vaccine Mandate for Athletes Like Kyrie Irving

🇺🇸💉@COVID19Up: Kyrie Irving and other unvaccinated athletes will finally be allowed to play professional sports in New York City under a major policy change Mayor Eric Adams is poised to announce on Thursday (March 24).

The mayor is expected to declare his decision to reverse the private-sector COVID-19 vaccine mandate specifically for performers and athletes in local venues, including Barclays Center—home to the Brooklyn Nets—and both Citi Field in Queens and Yankee Stadium in the Bronx.

The news comes on the heels of Adams’ announcement Tuesday (March 22) that he plans to lift the mask mandate for toddlers in city daycare centers on April 4.

Last Wednesday (March 16), Adams brushed aside questions about athletes who couldn't play professional sports in New York City due to their COVID-19 vaccination status.
